@SP

“What did the rest of you think?”

New PB. Two days in a row. 🤷‍♂️

@B
For last night's Elsbeth episode, the first 5 or so minutes was what had me rolling on the floor. Up to the first commercial break. By then I knew who was going to do it and to whom, anyway. 

I didn't know about Poker Face. If I can watch it without paying extra for it, I will. And if they get Dinklage to take over the role, I might even pay extra.

@Cindy
I don't think you have to watch them in order. There is a story arc involving her son that you won't get, at least initially, but the really entertaining part of this one is just the setting and the one-time characters.

There's also a little back story about why Elsbeth is there in the first place, but she is so outlandish, it really doesn't matter.

@SBK 

Totally with you on this! I am hoping another season of Poker Face comes out sometime soon, but I do enjoy Elsbeth! It's good fun!

Really enjoyed Natasha Lyonne in Russian Doll, as well! It's a little crazy, but my husband and I both really enjoyed it!

@Bob T.

The technical term for this, which I always find awkward, is "howcatchem".  Nothing has come close to classic Columbo, but the best of Poker Face is in the neighborhood.

@Lynn, after the 6th or 7th pay service and you still can't watch what you want, the "high seas" sirens come a calling.  We pay for "Peacock" but I'm not entirely sure why.

I love Dinklage but Lyonne has more than earned her right to the role.

@Your Fired
Congrats bro (gender neutral term). Actually, I guess I should say, mate. 
 I’m stoked for you. Make it a Saturday solve tomorrow!

