I was thinking, surely the difficulty level of this puzzle will please the super brains.

@Nancy

In Toronto, jiggly ladies fire T-shirts from cannons from atop the players' dugouts.

It is most compelling.

@Joan
It's not super brains for many (or most). It's super numbers of solved puzzles under the belt. You are doing the right things to get there!

I predict you'll get better month by month and then year by year. It's all in learning the kinds of tricks clue writers use to try to trip you up. If you are like me (and if they keep the puzzle difficulty up), you'll still get tricked even 10 years from. now, and enjoy it, but those tricks will feel like a hearty meal rather than a stone wall.

@Barry Ancona

Here I am. As I've mentioned before I carried an M-79 in Vietnam during my time there. Would be hard to even estimate how many rounds I fired during my time there, but I would guess it was over 200. (Oh - my company was called 'Hard-luck Alpha' because we were always in the wrong place at the wrong time). 

.....

